            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "I believe the correct answer here is that it returns a `RequestContext` as far as I see from the code, making the docstring for this function incorrect as well.\r\n\r\nIn `test_request_context()`:\r\n``` python\r\nreturn self.request_context(builder.get_environ())\r\n```\r\n\r\nIn `request_context()`:\r\n``` python\r\nreturn RequestContext(self, environ)\r\n```"
